Text.Value: We'll see you again, Astarion. This isn't over.
Astarion? It - it cannot be...
Walk to the window, into the sunlight.
No, you were a piece of shit. And you're still a piece of shit.
What Black Mass? What's Cazador planning?
Cazador's in the defiled chapel - beneath the palace.
You have no idea what I can do.
He's not telling the truth! And we don't need his help.
You're wasting your breath. We won't tell you anything.
We don't need another - the master said we have enough.
But if he is telling the truth, then he can prove it.
You're a monster! A freak!

EditorData.NodeContext: In pain, being burned by the sun

Text.Value: Fine, go and die for your master if that's what you want.
When has Astarion ever done anything that isn't in his own self-interest?
There won't be any Black Mass - I'm going to kill Cazador.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion grabs Petras by the throat and drags him over towards the window. Standing full in the daylight, Astarion slowly pulls Petras closer and closer to the sunbeam.
Both vampire spawn turn to mist and vanish, leaving just Astarion and the party in the room

Text.Value: And once it's done, he'll give us our freedom. He'll give us power.
Don't seek him, brother, please. He was so angry when you left.
Now that's funny. And the best part is you actually believe it.
You're all talk. You always were.
But it is. And as arrogant as ever.
I'm Cazador's doom.
Never.
*You know these people. Spawn, bound to Cazador, just as you once were.*
I have more than quips. You have no idea what I'm capable of.
Tell me what I need to know, or I swear you'll burn.
I'm gonna find you when the Mass is done, brother. Then you'll see what real power looks like.

EditorData.NodeContext: Recovering from Astarion (his brother) choking and burning him.

Text.Value: URRGH!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Held in the sunlight by Astarion, smoke starts to rise from Petras' face. He roars in pain.
EditorData.NodeContext: A vampire being burned by the sunlight

Text.Value: I can't believe you'd turn on us - on your own family.
Brother! You know we have no choice in this.
I trust him, Petras.
Let's go. We don't need to listen to this.
Don't be an idiot, Dal. He's all talk - always has been.
He's not our family. Not anymore.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion moves to the window and turns his face to the sun, smiling, then turns back to the vampire spawn. They're shocked.

Text.Value: The master has always been... strict. But we're better for it.
This isn't over. We'll see you again, 'brother'.
I'm not afraid of the old man.
What if he's telling the truth, Petras? He is free.
I'm something new.
He heard about the ritual and the power our master will grant us, so he came back with his tail between his legs, hoping all would be forgiven.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion forces Petra's face further into the sunlight streaming through the window. Smoke starts to rise from Petras' face.

Text.Value: I'll be blunt, then. Cazador plans to sacrifice us all at his 'ascension' ritual.
That's why we're worthy of freedom - of being elevated. And you're just a runt to be put down.
Nothing. Die if you want to, Petras.
You're just jealous. You lost your chance. You're not part of the family anymore.
As if you'd know the first thing about the master's plans. He's going to give us freedom - he's going to give us power.
I... I can't say you're wrong.
He'll destroy all of you if the Black Mass goes ahead.
And he promises that once he has ascended, he will give us our freedom.
Where is this ritual happening? Where can I find Cazador?
I want someone there, ready for me. Once the Mass is done and our master grants us our freedom, I'll want a drink.
Of course that's why he came crawling back. He wants to ascend with the rest of us.
You can't raise a hand to the master, let alone kill him.

EditorData.stateContext: Astarion holding Petras by the throat

Text.Value: Good.
I'm going to kill Cazador. Just tell me where to find him.
Elevated? You're deluded.
It's in all of our interests to see Cazador dead. We'll all be free.
You're proof of nothing. You're hiding in the shadows, just like the rest of us.
But when has the master ever rewarded us? When has he given us anything? And now he offers us freedom?
Tell me what I need to know, or I swear you'll burn.
Free to be hunted like a dog.
You're still the runt of the litter, Astarion. Nothing's changed.
Argh. ARGH!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Petras is starting to burn in the light

Text.Value: The Black Mass will be the master's greatest triumph. The ritual will see him ascend to power no vampire has ever known.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion tries to grab Petras, but he pushes him back and bares his fangs

Text.Value: If the Mass goes ahead, you'll be dead, not free. Cazador intends to sacrifice you.
You're lying - it can't be done.
Tell me where he is.
You can be free without him. You can be powerful without him - I am the proof.
Tell me about this 'ascension' - what's Cazador planning?
Kill the master? It's - it's not possible.
Cazador promised you freedom? And you believed him?
Cazador won't free you - he's going to sacrifice you in the ritual.
We'll see you soon, Astarion. I'm going to remember this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Resentful - still sore from being choked

Text.Value: You think you can just walk back in here with some stupid quip? On the eve of the master's ascension?
Astarion, please! I'll tell you everything - just release him!
The chapel has been there forever - hidden from all. There will be a sacrifice -

EditorData.NodeContext: Full sentence: "there will be a sacrifice and then the master will ascend", but gets cut off by Petra

Text.Value: Dalyria, I know you're smarter than this. Tell me what I need to know.
How could you say such things? We're family.
I admit, I wasn't the best brother to you, so let me make it up to you. Let me save you.
I'm the master now and you will obey.
Your only hope of freedom is his death. So tell me where he is.
You believe this? You believe that most self-centred, arrogant, egotistical one of us all is here to save the day?
Don't listen to him, Dal. We've been loyal - we've earned our reward. Unlike the runaway.
It's a trick - some glamour or spell. True power only comes from the master, and it will be ours soon.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion steps out of the sunlight and returns to his original staging/position.
EditorData.NodeContext: Shocked, trying to justify what he's just seen and reassure himself

Text.Value: The greatest vampire that ever lived.
Go on, 'brother'. Show us what you can do.
Sounds like a delightful dinner plan. Perhaps I'll join you.
Perhaps you should be. When the Black Mass is complete, he'll be stronger than ever.
Not if I kill him first. I just need to know where this 'Black Mass' is happening.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion releases Petras, tossing him back to original stage setting, standing by Dalyria

Text.Value: Please, Astarion. If you're telling the truth, please help us.
What the hells happened to you? What are you?

EditorData.NodeContext: recovering from Astarion's assault, shocked and scared

Text.Value: Dalyria - what are you doing?
When has Cazador given us anything other than beatings?
Show your face in the palace again and he'll punish you - destroy you.
You have no idea what I can do. Tell me where to find him or I'll make you pay.
I can show you real power. Right now.
Believe what you want - I'm done with you.
There's a defiled chapel under the master's palace - hidden there the entire time. That's where he's preparing the Black Mass.
Grab him by the throat and drag him towards the sunlight coming through the window.
How could you turn on us? We're family.

EditorData.NodeContext: Can't believe what Astarion's done, stress on 'family'

Text.Value: It's not for the master - it's for me. I spent one hundred years eating rats and dogs, but soon I'll be free to feast.
If you still serve him, I'll kill you too.
Why should Cazador ascend? I'd make a much better master than him.
We'll leave for the Black Mass soon. I only need one more mark.
You... you really think the master would kill us?
The sun can't harm me anymore.
The 'Master' promised you freedom? And you believed him?
How? It's not possible.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seeing Astarion standing in the sun without bursting into flames as a vampire should

Text.Value: Whatever changed you, brother - whatever you have become - the master still wants you. He will not stop looking for you.
Enough! Before you get us flayed alive.
Cazador's doom.
Listen to me, damn it! I'm trying to save you, even if you're too stupid to see it.
You have no idea what I can do.
Brother, please, just come home with us. There is no need to fight.
Hold him to the light.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion releases his hold on Petras's throat - he staggers away from the light coming through the window, doubled-over as he catches his breath

Text.Value: Let him go.
And you never will be. Come for him if you're stupid enough - he'll be waiting.

Synopsis:
Dalyria and Petras at the flophouse.
They are looking for Astarion at the place where they used to "hunt".
This is a dialog for when they meet Astarion-Avatar or Astarion-Companion with the player-Avatar.
They will tell Astarion they must inform Cazador that Astarion is back in the city. They will also reveal that Cazador is planning a ritual that requires all the spawn and that will grant them new powers.
If Astarion knows that Cazador is actually planning to sacrifice all the spawn, he might be able to convince the spawn about this sacrifice. In exchange, they will reveal a bit of information about Cazador's Palace.
After the dialog, they disappear as clouds of mist.
